Question: Should the government provide free college education to everyone the same way it provides high school education? Explain your answer.
Answer:
i don't think the government should do so. first of all, the fund for each college is really tight nowadays. in a university, except for undergraduate education, there are still plenty of researches going on. making college free to everyone to a large extent, also cuts off the money for other researches. second of all, without students paying tuitions, it is hard for faculty and staff to get paid.